author: Corey Pellatt
title: Calum Chambers and Alex Oxlade-Chamberlain's Game of Long-Rage Keep Ups Is the Best Football You'll See This W
text:
It turns out the most jaw-dropping thing to happen at the Emirates Stadium last weekend wasn't even Arsenal's 3-0 win over Manchester United.
Before the game, Alex Oxlade-Chamberlain and Calum Chambers took part in one of the most impressive game of keep ups we can remember seeing, smacking the ball to one another over 40 yards, without dropping it.
The Ox and Chambers are pretty tight in the dressing room.
We shouldn't be too surprised that the young England duo have struck up such an understanding.
In an interview with Complex UK this summer, Theo Walcott and Kieran Gibbs told us how Ox and Chambers have one of the Arsenal dressing room's biggest bromances.
[via Twitter ]
